div.p:
O wicked Spirit, here is true Piety; 
The Exorcist might have had more manners than to tell the Devil such a notorious lye to his face. 
Here is he who suffered for our Salvation. Now, faith he, shall the Prince of this World be cast forth. This is that Body which was taken from the Body of the Virgin, which was stretched out upon the Cross, which lay in the Grave; which rose from Death, and which ascended into Heaven in the sight of his Disciples; by the terrible Power of this Majesty, I command thee, wicked Devil, to depart from this Image of God, to fly from it, and never more to molest it.
